                    , large-scale and the small-scale vortical structures are well separated. This suggests that, during this stage, the energy transfer mechanism is non-local both in wavenumber and in physical space. On the other hand, as the spectrum becomes shallower and a
                    
                      ${k}^{\ensuremath{-} 5/ 3} $
                    
                    range appears, the energy-containing eddies and the small-scale vortices tend to be concentrated in the same regions, and structures with a wide range of sizes are observed, suggesting that the formation of an inertial range is accompanied by transfer of energy that is local in both physical and spectral space.
                  },
 author = {Orlandi, P. and Pirozzoli, S. and Carnevale, G. F.},
